      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Memory: validate dreaming cron frequency",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Validate `dreaming.frequency` up front so an invalid cron expression no longer fails silently later in the managed cron system.\n- Adds `validateMemoryDreamingFrequency()` to the memory host SDK; returns a discriminated `{ valid }` result with a `reason: \"inline-timezone\" | \"parse\" | \"timezone\"` so callers can tailor guidance.\n- Validator explicitly checks the IANA timezone via `Intl.DateTimeFormat` and forces `cron.nextRun(new Date())` after construction to defeat Croner's lazy-construction short-circuit.\n- `extensions/memory-core` calls the validator before creating/updating the managed dreaming cron job. On invalid input it logs an error and returns `{ status: \"invalid\", removed: 0 }`, intentionally leaving the last-known-good managed job untouched so dreaming keeps running until the config is fixed.\n- Inline `TZ=`/`CRON_TZ=` expressions get a targeted hint: `Timezone must be set via dreaming.timezone, not inline in the expression.` Plain parse errors do not.\n\n## Test plan\n- [x] `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/memory-host-sdk/dreaming.ts src/memory-host-sdk/dreaming.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.ts extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts`\n- [x] `corepack pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- [x] `corepack pnpm test src/memory-host-sdk/dreaming.test.ts`\n- [x] `corepack pnpm test extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts`\n- New tests cover: valid/invalid frequency validation, inline-timezone reason, invalid IANA timezone, plain-parse error does not surface timezone guidance, pre-existing managed cron job is preserved when the new config is invalid.",
